    public enum ContactStatus
extends java.lang.Enum<ContactStatus>

    The ContactStatus enum represents the status of a Contact.

    For the status of the authenticated user, see the Status enum.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      AVAILABLE

      BUSY
      Contact is online but currently busy.
      CONNECTING

      OFFLINE
      Contact is offline.
      STANDBY

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • AVAILABLE

        public static final ContactStatus AVAILABLE

        Contact is online and available to talk.

        Messages will be immediately delivered to a Contact with this status. Delivered messages will fire the Events.onMessageStateChanged() method.

        See Also:
        Events.onMessageStateChanged()

      • BUSY

        public static final ContactStatus BUSY

        Contact is online but currently busy.

        Messages will be delivered to the Zello for Work app of the Contact with this status, but they will not be delivered to the Zello SDK.

      • CONNECTING

        public static final ContactStatus CONNECTING

        Contact is currently connecting to the network.

        Messages sent to a Contact with this status will be delivered to the Zello SDK when they finish signing in. Delivered messages will fire the Events.onMessageStateChanged() method.

        See Also:
        Events.onMessageStateChanged()

      • OFFLINE

        public static final ContactStatus OFFLINE

        Contact is offline.

        Messages can potentially be delivered to a Contact with this status. If the Contact signs in before the user signs out, the message will be delivered to the Contact the next time they sign in.

      • STANDBY

        public static final ContactStatus STANDBY

        Contact is offline but was recently online.

        Messages sent to a Contact with this status will be delivered to the Zello SDK for the Contact the next time they sign in.
